As we grow into a generation where technology is key, we forget we live in a society where online safety is not guaranteed. Yes our internet banking is regulated with passwords and back-up passwords and perhaps a line of security questions, but we often give away information that we really do not need to. Remember back in the day when parents would warn their children not to mention that they are alone at home when the phone rang, in case it was a burglar that wanted to invade the property when the child was most vulnerable? Today the same premise counts, only, the internet had become your metaphorical telephone.You might be fooled by these scamsPeople do stock trading, investments, banking and shopping online. Everywhere, someone is watching if you are leaving a backdoor open when you leave the site. Follow these tips from the experts:When banking:When trading/investing:When shoppingWhen doing general things on your smartphone/computer